    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The in-circumcircle test uses a 4x4 determinant reduced to a 3x3 form. The sign convention assumes counter-clockwise vertex ordering; swap any two vertices and the sign flips. The lifting-to-paraboloid construction is exact: the lower convex hull facets in 3D correspond bijectively to Delaunay triangles in 2D. This is the basis of the fastest known Delaunay algorithms (via 3D convex hull in expected O(n log n)).</p>

